B.  Technical and Logistical Services and Support 

1.  Regional Cooperation Advisor (national, 30 person-months) 
6.  A regional cooperation advisor based in ADB headquarters will  
(i)  provide advice on matters related to TA administration, including the coordination, 
consolidation, and monitoring of various activities under the TA;  
(ii)  assist in preparing regional cooperation operations business plans for South Asia; 
(iii)  assist in formulating the new regional cooperation strategy for South Asia;  
(iv)  prepare  background  papers,  briefing  papers,  and  presentation  materials  for 
meetings, conferences, and other TA events; 
(v)  review, comment on, and edit consultants' reports and other documents and 
papers as required; 
(vi)  prepare and update progress reports on TA activities and related projects, as 
well as newsletters and other publications as required; 
(vii)  prepare semiannual progress reports and summaries of proceedings of meetings, 
in coordination and consultation with ADB focal persons; 
(viii)  assist in implementing TA activities and meetings, as well as joint activities with 
other regional cooperation programs; and 
(ix)  participate in and assist ADB missions, conferences, workshops, seminars, and 
meetings. 

2.  Regional Cooperation Specialist (national, 30 person-months) 
7.  A regional cooperation specialist will be based in ADB headquarters and  
(i)  assist  in  carrying  out  studies  and  papers  related  to  regional  cooperation, 
including project profiles of regional projects; 
(ii)  assist in preparing regional cooperation operations business plans for South Asia;  
(iii)  assist in formulating the new regional cooperation strategy for South Asia;  
(iv)  prepare presentations and papers relating to regional cooperation activities in 
South Asia; 
(v)  develop, maintain, and update the information system and webpage covering all 
TA activities; 
(vi)  prepare monitoring reports and coordinate with participating countries and sector 
experts on TA implementation matters; 
(vii)  assist in organizing meetings and other regional cooperation activities; and 
(viii)  participate in and assist ADB missions, conferences, workshops, seminars, and 
meetings.  

3.  Program Analyst and/or Regional Cooperation Expert (national, 30 person-
months) 
8.  A senior program analyst and/or regional cooperation expert based in ADB headquarters 
